Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @sweet potatoes{2} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Finely chop @pepitas{1/2%ounce} (or crush in their bag with a heavy-bottomed pan or rolling pin). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss sweet potatoes on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @harissa powder{1/2%tsp} (or more if you want an extra kick!), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

While sweet potatoes roast, place garlic and @butter{1.5%tablespoon} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until butter is melted, ~{30-45%seconds}. Let cool slightly, then stir in pepitas, remaining oregano, @panko breadcrumbs{3%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, half the @red pepper jam{1}, @harissa powder{1/4%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. (Taste and add more harissa if you like.) If needed, add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Drizzle skin sides with oil; rub to coat.

Once sweet potatoes have roasted 12 minutes, remove #sheet{} from oven. Carefully push sweet potatoes to one side of sheet; place salmon, skin sides down, on empty side. (For 4 servings, transfer sweet potatoes to middle rack; add salmon to a second sheet and roast on top rack.) Evenly spread tops of salmon with a thin layer of @dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}; sprinkle with a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and mound with pepita mixture, pressing firmly to adhere.

Roast on top rack until crust is golden brown and salmon is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a second small bowl, whisk together remaining jam, @olive oil{1.5%teaspoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> For a tangier dressing, add another squeeze of lemon juice.

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce}, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and tomatoes with as much dressing as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide salmon, sweet potatoes, and salad between plates. Drizzle salmon with as much sauce as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges and any remaining sauce on the side.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.